{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"1V9tDyQwkgBuhWMngZc6p","title":"Limit Theorems","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"type":"note","desc":"","links":[],"anchors":{"central-limit-theorem":{"type":"header","text":"Central Limit Theorem","value":"central-limit-theorem","line":8,"column":0},"law-of-large-numbers":{"type":"header","text":"Law of Large Numbers","value":"law-of-large-numbers","line":10,"column":0},"slutskycontinuous-mapping-theorem":{"type":"header","text":"Slutsky/Continuous Mapping Theorem","value":"slutskycontinuous-mapping-theorem","line":18,"column":0},"cramer-wold-device":{"type":"header","text":"Cramer-Wold Device","value":"cramer-wold-device","line":30,"column":0},"":{"type":"header","text":"","value":"","line":32,"column":0}},"fname":"Appendix.Limit_theorems","updated":1636418351270,"created":1636344103536,"parent":"CQTUwoXQNcd0Y7la7IaAn","children":[],"data":{},"contentHash":"a42bdcc20380e88baadc5364d99805ef","custom":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"limit-theorems\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#limit-theorems\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Limit Theorems</h1>\n<h2 id=\"central-limit-theorem\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#central-limit-theorem\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Central Limit Theorem</h2>\n<h2 id=\"law-of-large-numbers\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#law-of-large-numbers\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Law of Large Numbers</h2>\n<p>There are different sets of sufficient conditions for the WLLN.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Kolmogorov, all X are i.i.d. with finite expectation. Note that this implies the SLLN.</li>\n<li>Chebyshev, all X are uncorrelated, such that the variance is finite, and the sample variance converges to 0 asymptotically</li>\n<li>All X have finite variance, and sample variance converges to 0 asymptotically. Additionally, all sample covariances, and the sum of all sample covariances are finite (looser version of the Chebyshev version).</li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"slutskycontinuous-mapping-theorem\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#slutskycontinuous-mapping-theorem\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Slutsky/Continuous Mapping Theorem</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>If <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>X</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo><mover><mo><mo>→</mo></mo><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>s</mi></mrow></mover></mo><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X_n \\overset{as}{\\rightarrow} X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.1182619999999999em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.151392em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:-0.07847em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">n</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\"><span class=\"mop op-limits\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.968262em;\"><span style=\"top:-3em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span><span class=\"mop\">→</span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.5668699999999998em;margin-left:0em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">a</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">s</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span></span>, <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>f</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><msub><mi>X</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo><mover><mo><mo>→</mo></mo><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>s</mi></mrow></mover></mo><mi>f</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>X</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">f(X_n) \\overset{as}{\\rightarrow} f(X)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.218262em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.151392em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:-0.07847em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">n</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\"><span class=\"mop op-limits\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.968262em;\"><span style=\"top:-3em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span><span class=\"mop\">→</span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.5668699999999998em;margin-left:0em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">a</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">s</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></span></li>\n<li>If <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>X</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo><mover><mo><mo>→</mo></mo><mi>p</mi></mover></mo><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X_n \\overset{p}{\\rightarrow} X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.16537em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.151392em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:-0.07847em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">n</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\"><span class=\"mop op-limits\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:1.01537em;\"><span style=\"top:-3em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span><span class=\"mop\">→</span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.613978em;margin-left:0em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">p</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span></span>, <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>f</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><msub><mi>X</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo><mover><mo><mo>→</mo></mo><mi>p</mi></mover></mo><mi>f</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>X</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">f(X_n) \\overset{p}{\\rightarrow} f(X)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.26537em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.151392em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:-0.07847em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">n</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\"><span class=\"mop op-limits\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:1.01537em;\"><span style=\"top:-3em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span><span class=\"mop\">→</span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.613978em;margin-left:0em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">p</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></span></li>\n<li>If <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>X</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo><mover><mo><mo>→</mo></mo><mi>d</mi></mover></mo><mi>X</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">X_n \\overset{d}{\\rightarrow} X</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.302978em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.151392em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:-0.07847em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">n</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\"><span class=\"mop op-limits\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:1.152978em;\"><span style=\"top:-3em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span><span class=\"mop\">→</span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.5668699999999998em;margin-left:0em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">d</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span></span></span></span></span>, <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>f</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><msub><mi>X</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo><mover><mo><mo>→</mo></mo><mi>d</mi></mover></mo><mi>f</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>X</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">f(X_n) \\overset{d}{\\rightarrow} f(X)</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.402978em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.151392em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.5500000000000003em;margin-left:-0.07847em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">n</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\"><span class=\"mop op-limits\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:1.152978em;\"><span style=\"top:-3em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span><span class=\"mop\">→</span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.5668699999999998em;margin-left:0em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">d</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></span></li>\n</ol>\n<p>Part 3 is called the Continuous Mapping Theorem. Part 1 is called Slutsky's Theorem.</p>\n<p>However, both can be referred to as the Continuous Mapping Theorem, because Slutsky's Theorem is a really just a special case of the broader CMT.</p>\n<p>Note that the above is a very simplified version! To get the more complicated versions which we typically apply, you will need to define <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>f</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">f()</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span></span> in a special way, e.g. <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>f</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi>X</mi><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>X</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>Y</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">f(X) = X + Y</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.10764em;\">f</span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2777777777777778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.76666em;vertical-align:-0.08333em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07847em;\">X</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222222222222222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.22222em;\">Y</span></span></span></span></span> where <span class=\"math math-inline\"><span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>Y</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">Y</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.68333em;vertical-align:0em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.22222em;\">Y</span></span></span></span></span> is some other random variable.</p>\n<h2 id=\"cramer-wold-device\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#cramer-wold-device\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a>Cramer-Wold Device</h2>\n<h2 id=\"\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading\" href=\"#\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\"><use xlink:href=\"#svg-link\"></use></svg></a></h2>","noteIndex":{"id":"PhD","title":"PhD Homepage","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"type":"note","desc":"","links":[{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"root","id":"PhD","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"user.han_tests_201